I had my order delivered. Compared to the other Chinese restaurants in the neighborhood, I thought Happy Wok's food was good. I got mixed vegetables in garlic sauce (was a bit too sweet -- I ended up picking out the vegetables from the sauce) over brown rice (yes, they have brown rice!!!).  My fiance got beef with broccoli in black bean sauce (too salty for me) over vegetable fried rice (a little bland). We both thought it was ok, and definitely better than some of the other places in the neighborhood. The delivery guy was pretty friendly as well.  All in all, a pleasant experience.
